$ git init												--> Used to initialize empty Git repository

$ git clone https://github.com/ramugubbala/Dataengineer.git 	--> Cloning remote repository into local machine.

$ cd Dataengineer

$ ls -ltr

$ git add new_files										--> Add new files to the local git repository
or
$ git add .												--> Period is used to add multiple files to the repository

$ git commit -m "commit message added new file"			--> Commit is used to add final changes to the local repository

$ git status											--> Status will show the current branch

$ git push origin master								--> Push is used to publish local commits to the remote server

$ git pull												--> Pull is used to download the latest files from remote server


### New folder and New files connection

Step1: Create a new folder in your local machine repository
Step2: Go to the new folder and type "git init" to initialize the repository

$ git init

$ git remote add origin https://github.com/ramugubbala/Dataengineer.git  --> Map the remote repository to the new folder

$ git pull origin master								--> To download all the files from remote server to local

### Add or modify the files and save

$ git add new_files										--> Add new files to the local git repository
or
$ git add .												--> Period is used to add multiple files to the repository

$ git commit -m "commit message added new file"			--> Commit is used to add final changes to the local repository

$ git status											--> Status will show the current branch

$ git push origin master								--> Push is used to publish local commits to the remote server

### To import new changes or files, go to your folder

$ cd Dataengineer

$ git pull

